Infotexts.ntg.description.surgical_infection:
Surgical Infection is a mechanic that causes Sepsis based on how sterile the patient's environment is during surgery.
    \nThe following things will increase Sterility:
    - The patient is wearing Surgical Drapes (+100 base Sterility);
    - Nearby characters that are wearing a Surgical Mask and Surgeon Clothes (scales with distance to the patient);
    - Having Surgery Skill (sterility gained based off this equation: 10 + surgery skill / 5);
    - Having Ointmented (from Antibiotic Ointment / Antiseptic) on the Surgery Incision (+50 sterility).
    \nThe following things will increase Sterility:
    - The patient having no Surgical Drapes (Sterility set to minimum)
    - Nearby characters that are not wearing a Surgical Mask and Surgeon Clothes (scales with distance to the patient).
